      <title>Is the definition of shaman</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&amp;message.id=6096#M6096</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;to be Sony's year long April Fools target?  What's up with Sony and Shaman spell progression?  Everyone remember PoP?  They had to totally rewrite our spells because their progression sucked so much.  They had to merge two spells and give us a totally new one.  Now we get OoW 2, almost 3 expansions ago, and they did it again with Champion and Group Might.  Our last spell is inclusive in the 4th spell?  Whats up with that?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;And why is that that 2 almost three epxansions later level 70 shaman mains STILL don't have all their non-ancient spells from that expansion?  Its time for SoE to start looking at Rune drops and really Upping them.  This is ridiculous.  At this point what I want most is a quest to allow you to turn in a 66, 67, and 68 rune to be fashioned into either a 69 or 70, or something.  Why does Sony always drop the ball on retuning expansions that have been out a while, especially ones that raise the level cap, to allow for the changing economy needs after we've attained the new cap?  Remember when Kunark came out?  How much was Singing Steel armor?  How much was Cobalt?  How many Bards on your server?  How many warriors?  This is the same stupid thing.  How many level 66-68 mains are on your server? How many 69-70?&lt;/div&gt;</description>
