    <item>
      <title>What is a shaman?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=shamanbalance&amp;message.id=6050#M6050</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT size=2&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;During my 6 years of playing a shaman in Norrath I am asked on a regular basis "What is a shaman's role?" by people who are new to the shaman class or who are just curious. So I figured I would write this post to try to help explain our class and our role.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Now to start off the shaman fits many roles. We are what most would consider a 'support' class which means in a nut shell we don't make the group we just make the group better. Originally the direction SOE had for the shaman was to be the ultimate melee class buffer, which arguably is the truth. There isn't an hour that goes by that I am in PoK that I don't get sent a few tells asking for my buffs, which are some of the best in game hands down. Our buffs can bring up your STR, AGI, DEX, STA, AC, HP, CHR, they can speed up your attacks and bring up your resists. In short this is just some of our buffing abilities. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Another of our fine abilities is healing. Our heals aren't up to speed with the clerics or even with druids but we can heal and we are usually used as back up healers in a group with either a cleric or a druid as main healer. As healing goes we have a line that does heal over time which is great to cast on a tank as the pull is incoming to off set the damage he will take while you are trying to get the mob slowed. Along with our healing spells is our healing AAs which we have a couple of. Ancestrial Aid is a good group heal which can be used in an emergency and is instant cast which can mean the difference between pulling it off or wiping and summoning the corpses.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;But buffing and healing is only a small portion of what makes a shaman a desired class so lets look at the offensive capabilities of our class. We have what SOE considers to be the most powerful spell line in the game hands down and that is our Turgurs line or our Slow. When in a combat situation a shaman can slow all his enemies attack speed by 75%, considering that is what the spell was designed to land at. SOE has for years now felt that this spell is too powerful and added ways to limit the ability of our slow spells, from making mobs immune to changes in speed, to upping their MR so it has basically no chance of landing, to having mobs mitigate the slows to almost nothing.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Now lets not forget about the shaman DoTs. Our DoT spells are some of the best out there second only to the necro. We have mainly poison and disease but we do have a few magic based curses which are basically short term but they do deal decent amount of damage in the 5 to 6 tics it is on the mob for. With the low actual combat DPS we put out, these DoTs bring up our DPS quite a bit.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We also have a pet to help with DPS out put. Now our pets in no way can stand up to most pets like say with a mage pet or a necro pet but they do add a bit more DPS and when solowing these pets will help out quite a bit.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Shaman can also play the part of crowed control. We have numerous root spells and with our chain armor we can take a few hits before we go down so it is natural to use the shaman on crowd control. We also have an AA called Virulent Paralysis that will root a mob and our PoP armor also has a right click root effect on it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So in short our class can play many roles in a group and just remember a Shaman doesn't make the group we just make the group stronger.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Bombados Kindheart&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Level 70 Shaman&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The Tribunal server&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
